Why would a rich person rob a grocery store when they could embezzle the funds they need?  The two socioeconomic groups may not commit the exact same crimes all the time, but they still commit crime.  The crimes typically committed by the upper middle class tend to be the traditional white collar crimes.  One is easier to bust and prosecute than the other.
